How to fix your hair in a week 🌺

EPISODE 6/7 

It is very important to follow the exact steps below to make sure you get non frizzy hair that look like you’ve done a blow out. 

1. Use @moxiebeautyofficial leave in conditioner. Take a small dollop and apply it on wet hair. Let it soak in for a minute. 

2. Use the @moxiebeautyofficial frizz fighting serum and rake it thru your wet hair. This makes sure you get glossy non frizzy hair once it dries. 

3. Use a @dyson_india volumizing brush and dry your hair fully. 

4. Use the leave in hair oil from @moroccanoil_in I love this one because it’s very lightweight and it locks the moisture  in your hair. 

#shorthairideas #indianhairbrand #frizzfreehair #frizzfreecurls

How to fix your hair in week 🌺

EPISODE 5/7 

Dandruff is very common in India especially cause we live in a very dry and hot/cold environment. I used to get dry scalp and dandruff using the winters till I found this method to fix it and I haven’t had it since then. 

1. I use the @consciouschemistindia glycolic acid serum for scalp 15 mins before shampoo.

2. I use a ketoconazole shampoo and leave it on for 5 mins before washing it off. This prevents bacteria from thriving and also promotes hair growth. 

3. I use the @moxiebeautyofficial shampoo to cleanse scalp a second time. I notice a huge difference in scalp oiliness if I don’t double shampoo.

4. Before coming out of the shower I rinse my hair with diluted apple cider vinegar for 2 mins and then rinse with cold water. 

#dandruff #dandrufftreatment #dryscalp #indianhaircare

latestPosts.caption:
How to fix your hair in a week 🌺

EPISODE 3/7 

AYURVEDIC HAIR GROWTH 💖

I had insane hair fall last year due to trauma from abuse in a relationship. After it ended I had to figure out how to make my hair healthy again. I now have healthy hair again so I’ve put everything I know in this caption. 🍀

I have even more information in my hair care guide so comment if you want the link to that. 🧡

1. I used the @indewild champi hair oil with Bhringraj, Brahmi, Amla and Neem for the first few months but then I made some modifications to it. 🥥 

I heated the oil with curry leaves, methi, kalonji, and onion. I then added some rosemary essential oil to it. These ingredients are mentioned in ayurveda as being very powerful for hair growth. I now use this oil twice a week to oil my hair. 🧅 

2. I promote blood flow in the scalp and stimulate the hair roots by massaging my scalp and then derma rolling with a 1.5mm roller before I oil my hair. There are 3 spots on the scalp - Adhipati, Simantaka and Krikatika that you should focus on while massaging. 

3. I drink the @drsu.formulations grow and glow powder which has Ashwagandha, moringa and Amla. I also take bhringraj powder separately and eat Amla in the winters. These herbs are mentioned in ayurveda for promoting insane hair growth. 

4. The root cause of hair loss in men is the increase in DHT which means thicker hair on face but thinner hair on scalp. Since I had pcos (healed that naturally) I eat DHT blocking foods like mango, pumpkin seeds and 3 cups of green tea everyday. 🥭 

5. Finally the best thing that happened was I found a video on YouTube which helped calm my body that had been in constant panic mode for years. If your body is flooded with cortisol it’s going to focus on vital functions only and hair growth isn’t a vital function. Cortisol also impacts hair and skin deeply. 

I do the meditation everyday and it has healed my acne, hair and slowly my anxiety. If you want the link to this let me know in the comment please. 🌺

#haircaretips #ayurvedichaircare #indianhaircare #healingfromtrauma

EPISODE 2/7

I have used these 2 hair serums and seen great results with both of them. I had very damaged hair last year and now I have thick healthy hair. 

1. @indewild moonlight hair serum with Bhringraj, moringa, Amla and Brahmi. It also has chemicals known to grow hair including Redensyl and Baicapil. 🧡

2. @mywishcare hair growth serum with caffeine, biotin, rice water, Redensyl, Baicapil and Anagain. 🍀

I have noticed baby hair growing and less hair fall as soon as I started using both products. I started with Wishcare and then switched to Inde Wild because it has Ayurvedic as well which I love.
